 While Cicero's Judicial Theater will be of interest primarily to professional scholars and students studying the speeches of Cicero, its wider analyses, both of Roman cultural customs and the idiosyncratic practices of the law-courts, will prove relevant also to social historians, as well as historians of legal procedure"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on information from the publisher.10aCicero, Marcus Tullius.tSpeeches. 0aSpeeches, addresses, etc., LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aOratory, Ancient. 0aTheaterzRome. 4aElectronic books.2 aMichigan Publishing (University of Michigan)epublisher.40zAccess to the Michigan Publishing online version:uhttps://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.1879571